  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "structural steel Erector",
  "description": "<h3><strong>Structural Steel Erector – Job Duties & Responsibilities</strong></h3><ul><li><p>Read and interpret <strong>structural drawings, blueprints, and erection plans</strong></p></li><li><p><strong>Unload, sort, and position steel components</strong> (beams, columns, braces, trusses)</p></li><li><p><strong>Rig, hoist, and align structural steel members</strong> using cranes, slings, chains, and cables</p></li><li><p><strong>Bolt, weld, and secure steel structures</strong> according to engineering specifications</p></li><li><p>Ensure steel members are <strong>level, plumb, and properly aligned</strong></p></li><li><p>Install <strong>metal decking, stairs, handrails, and miscellaneous steel</strong></p></li><li><p>Perform <strong>field welding and cutting</strong> using oxy-fuel, plasma, or arc welding equipment</p></li><li><p><strong>Inspect steel connections</strong> for accuracy, strength, and safety compliance</p></li><li><p>Follow <strong>site safety rules</strong>, OSHA regulations, and company safety procedures</p></li><li><p>Use <strong>power tools and hand tools</strong> safely and efficiently</p></li><li><p>Work at <strong>heights using harnesses, lifts, and scaffolding</strong></p></li><li><p>Coordinate with <strong>crane operators, supervisors, and other trades</strong></p></li><li><p>Identify and report <strong>structural defects or misalignments</strong></p></li><li><p>Assist in <strong>temporary bracing and stabilization</strong> of structures</p></li><li><p>Maintain a <strong>clean and safe worksite</strong></p></li><li><p>Perform <strong>basic equipment maintenance</strong> and report malfunctions</p></li></ul>",
